Markdown is a text-to-HTML conversion tool for web writers. Markdown allows you to write using an easy-to-read, easy-to-write plain text format, then convert it to structurally valid XHTML(or HTML).

MARKDOWN SYNTAX

Italics
*This text will appear italicized!*

Bold
**This text will appear bold!**

Headings
# This is a main headings - Largest header
## This is a secondary headings - middle header
### This is a tertiary headings - smallest header

Unordered Lists
- first item in list
- second item in list
- third item in list

Ordered Lists
1. first item in list
2. second item in list
3. third item in list

Links
[John Hopkins Bloomberg School of Public Health](http://www.jhsph.edu/)
[Download R](http://www.r-project.org/)
[rStudio](http://www.rstudio.com/)

Advanced Links
I spend so much time reading [R bloggers][1] and [Simply Statistics[2][2]!
[1]: https://www.r-bloggers.com/ "R bloggers"
[2]: https://simplystatistics.org/ "Simply Statistics"

Newlines
-Newlines require a double space after the end of a line

